<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1259">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/415.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s August 22, regarding payment of mining taxes in Mexico
                            Department’s objection is sustained, exception being made of cases in
                            which payments were made to Huerta officials when they could have been
                            made to Constitutionalist authorities in territory occupied by the
                            Constitutionalists. For instance taxes on Sonora properties paid to
                            Huerta authorities in Mexico City would not be considered valid.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>